### Configure GitHub Auth via Supabase Management API (Bash)

Source: https://github.com/supabase/supabase/blob/master/apps/docs/content/guides/auth/social-login/auth-github.mdx

This snippet demonstrates how to enable and configure the GitHub authentication provider for a Supabase project using the Supabase Management API via cURL. It requires Supabase access token and project reference, and accepts GitHub client ID and secret as JSON payload.

```bash
# Get your access token from https://supabase.com/dashboard/account/tokens
export SUPABASE_ACCESS_TOKEN="your-access-token"
export PROJECT_REF="your-project-ref"

# Configure GitHub auth provider
curl -X PATCH "https://api.supabase.com/v1/projects/$PROJECT_REF/config/auth" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer $SUPABASE_ACCESS_TOKEN" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "external_github_enabled": true,
    "external_github_client_id": "your-github-client-id",
    "external_github_secret": "your-github-client-secret"
  }'
```

