### PATCH /v1/projects/{PROJECT_REF}/config/auth

Source: https://github.com/supabase/supabase/blob/master/apps/docs/content/guides/auth/social-login/auth-github.mdx

Configures the GitHub authentication provider settings for a Supabase project using the Management API. This allows you to enable GitHub login and set your application credentials.

```APIDOC
## PATCH /v1/projects/{PROJECT_REF}/config/auth

### Description
Configures the GitHub authentication provider settings for a Supabase project. This allows you to enable GitHub login, set your client ID, and client secret.

### Method
PATCH

### Endpoint
https://api.supabase.com/v1/projects/{PROJECT_REF}/config/auth

### Parameters
#### Path Parameters
- **PROJECT_REF** (string) - Required - The unique reference ID of your Supabase project.

#### Headers
- **Authorization** (string) - Required - Your Supabase access token, prefixed with `Bearer`.
- **Content-Type** (string) - Required - Must be `application/json`.

#### Request Body
- **external_github_enabled** (boolean) - Required - Set to `true` to enable GitHub authentication for the project.
- **external_github_client_id** (string) - Required - The client ID obtained from your GitHub OAuth application.
- **external_github_secret** (string) - Required - The client secret obtained from your GitHub OAuth application.

### Request Example
```json
{
  "external_github_enabled": true,
  "external_github_client_id": "your-github-client-id",
  "external_github_secret": "your-github-client-secret"
}
```

### Response
#### Success Response (200)
This endpoint typically returns an empty body or a confirmation of the updated configuration upon successful update.

#### Response Example
```json
{}
```
```

